<head>
<style>
h1 { background-color:purple;}
p{color:red; front-size:25px; front-family:arial;}
</style>
</head>

properties
border-botton:1px solid black;

Css inheritance
HTML
|
head  \body
|
h1 p p h2
add property to parent, child inherits the same property

class
p.classname{
property
}

In body
<body>
<p class= "classname">
content</p>
aquires the properities of above mentioned class

<p class="classname"> content
<blockquote>
content  #this content will not hold the properties of the class
</blockquote>
</p>

in order to have the properties of another class
<blockquote class= "newclassname">

for underline
.underline{
text-decoration:underline
}
<p class blue underline>

Font
font family: verdana, arial, geneva, arial black
body{
font-weight:lighter; } (normal,body, bolder)

style sheet
1. internal style sheet - good for one page
2. External style sheet -if it has many pages
3. Inline style sheet - directly into html code

external style sheet -> sheetname.css
no need <style> tag
body{
}
<link rel= "stylesheet"type="text/css" href="name.css">

